PLACES:

    Galios:
        - The main world that the story takes place in, Galios is similar to Earth in
	many aspects, but also very different. Galios is presented as a "flat" world by
	pretty much every map, but it is round like Earth. Galios has no concept of seasons
	weather in areas stays the same. Also, islands tend to have their own climate system.

	Roniel:
	    - The main continent that the game takes place in, it is the largest
	    landmass in all of Galios, with most of the surface of Galios being
	    covered in water.
    
    Valaar:
        - Another world, the Durmians come here on their voyage and by the time
        they arrive the corruption of their artifical society spreads to the planet
        and turns it into a hellish world filled with monsters, and causing severe
	pollution from the corrupt Aetherium they generated.
        
    

CIVILIZATIONS:

- All civilizations/peoples are human unless stated otherwise.

    Protohuman (Inusol):
        - The ancient precursor race of the Durmia people, very little
        is known about them and they remain shrouded in mystery having existed
        long before the Durmians have.
        Inusol civilization was technologically advanced, remaining architecture
        appears to made of Beige colored sandstone, inidicating that Inusol people
        were mainly desert dwelling, building cities etched into the sandstone
        of the desert faces.
	Most (or all) current remnants of this civilization reside in the desert,
	suggesting that they may have occupied the vast deserts.
        
        
    Modern:
        - the current civlizations inhabiting the world, there are multiple sub
        civilizations that exist:
        
        Kingdom of Altaria:
            - the main people that the player is introduced to, the character
            himself is Altarian.
	    The Kingdom of Altaria is a Monarchy, divided into provinces that are governed
	    by Archlords, and cities in each province governed by Mayors.
	    In the case of Provincial Captials, the Archlord servers as a mayor
	    as well as a governer of the province, with an appointed Count to help
	    advise the Archlord with city matters.
	    In the special case of the City of Gondale, the King himself resides in
	    Gondale, with an Archlord also residing in Gondale, together the King rules
	    over Altaria with the Archlord of Gondale serving under The King, worrying
	    about provinical matters and municipal matters.
    
                Province of Soulnar:
                    - Soulnarian people are a small group of Altarians that live in a
		    closed off reigon near a lake leading to an ocean, mountains
		    surround the area making travel outside and inside difficult.
		    Due to the secluded nature of this province, they are largely
		    uninvolved with the ongoing civil war.

		    Nulport City:
		        (based off of Venice, sort of)
		        - The main city of Soulnar which resides in the south end of
			Soulnar, right on the water in a huge gulf leading to the ocean.
			Soulnar is a port city which relies on it's fishing market and
			mineral trade. Minerals are mined from the nearby mountains,
			which is mostly coal.

		   Coalshard Mine:
		        - a mine located in the shadow of the Soulnar mountains, the
			majority of Soulnar's mining industry comes from here.
			The mine contains mostly coal with some other minerals.
                
                Province of Morrodel:
                    - The largest population of Altarians, they mostly reside in
		    the Greenlands with settlments and structures going from the mid
		    of the Greenlands and some structures extending to the Boreanlands.
		    Years ago, the Province mostly was located near the edge of the
		    Greenlands and Borean lands, but the city of Etmoya gained immense
		    treasures and resources, which lead to Morrodel buying out many
		    sections of Maldrell that extended into the Greenlands, this played
		    a part in starting the civil war.
		    Morrodel informally is the leading province although it does not
		    contain the Captial City of Altaria, which is another reason for
		    the ongoing civil war. The Archlord of Morrodel wants to become
		    the King of Altaria, which also naturally would contribute.
		    Morrodelians have mostly brown or dark colored hair.
                
                    City of Etmoya:

		    Port Novadago
		    	(based off of Nova Scotia)
		        - The largest port city in all of Altaria, many shipping
			companies and sailors have their businesses located here, it is
			located on the east coast of Roniel in a huge bay.
			With the smell of the ocean, the sound of seagulls, and the
			impressive harbour of sea vessels; many sailors, seamen, explorers,
			and the like are attracted to Port Novadago for its opportunites.
                
                Province of Maldrell:
                    - Sister province of Morrodel, not as big as the province of
		    Morrodel but still big, it mostly spans the Greenlands, with some parts
		    in the Boreanlands. The province used to posses more land in the
		    Greenlands but a lot of it was bought out by Morrodel.
		    Formally, it is the leading province of Altaria but in actuality
		    Morrodel has more power and influcence with it's great city of Etmoya.
		    Maldrellians are mostly blonde in hair color.

		    City of Gondale:
		    	 - Largest city of Maldrell, and the second largest in
			 all of Altaria. It is the captial city of Altaria, although
			 being less impressive than Etmoya, is still a great city.
			 The city resides central-east in the province of Maldrell, near
			 the border between Morrodel and Maldrell, in the great grasslands.
			 King Aaylem rules in his palace, with the Archlord of Gondale
			 residing in his keep opposite of the Kings Palace.
			 As the Capital City of Altaria during the civil war,
			 it is a highly contested city at the time of the game.

		    Cadenville:
		        - a town known for it's prestigous knight academy, young
			squires come here to train as soldiers and knights for the Maldrell
			army, the best going to Gondale to become Royal Guards.

		Province of Torensho:
		    - A medium sized province mostly spanning the south and east parts of
		    Altaria.
                
                Province of Orshaw:
                    - A small province in the Tundra, mostly isolated and cold.
		    Travel between this province and the others is difficult
		    due to the harsh weather and terrain.
        
        Kingdom of Mordia:
            - Mordian people are much different than Altarian, being completey seperate and
            not having much communtication between kingdoms. They are slighty more advanced
	    with their technology and lifestyle compared to Altarians.
	    Mordia lies on a huge land mass very far to the west, separated by the ocean.

	Oraban Tribe:
	    - A great tribe mostly dwelling in the vast desert to the south, they rival
	    Altaria in power and number, and have had conflict with Altaria before.

	Sokorea Nation:
	    (based off of Korea, Japan)
	    - A small group of peaceful people who live on a large forested peninsula in the
	    shadow of a massive mountain range to the north/northwest. They mostly
	    are cutoff from the other civilizaitons, due to the mostly unpassable
	    mountain range lying to the north, keeping others from discovering Sokorea.
	    On the other side of the mountain range, is a quasi desert, probably caused
	    due to the mountains blocking the moisture.
	    Sokrean people may be direct descedants of Dur Vahltan people.

	    Saito Kunista:
	        - a coast village located in a eastern nook on the peninsula, located on
	    	a slope towards the sea. The village is quiet and mostly contains aging
	    	residents who retire in the peace of the warm breezes coming from the sea.
		The village also has a harbour for fisherman and sailors.

	    Nakatora City:
	        (based off of Seoul, Tokyo)
	        - The largest city in Sokorea, located on the south end of the Sokorean
		peninsula right on a river coming from the ocean. The city is slighty
		inland, but not too far from the ocean.
		Known for it's lively beauty (especially at night with the special firefly
		lanterns), and the beatiful pink sakura blossoms.

	    Takusa:
		- a small village in the north forested hills of Sokorea. The dragon legends
		of Sokrea have the strongest presence here (since the dragon was said to
		come down from the mountain, which this village is closest to).
                
        
        Inusol (modern):
            - remnants of a faction of Protohumans (Inusol) that broke off long ago.
            They live in the former Inusol desert city known as Daascae.
            They dress in white and gold and live complete seperate from the rest of the
	    world.

	    Daascae:
	        - A desert city built into a huge sandstone outcropping, the city is
		shaped like an inverted cone, with residents living along the mountain
		side, and a central stone piece at the lowest point in the city.
		The central stone piece house a temple thought to once dwell in the sky,
		but now has returned to rest in the sand, the people of Daascae believe
		that it will rise once again.
		And to justify the myth, there is a giant stone etching showing a huge
		structure lifting out of Daascae and rising towards the sky.

		Aureola Keep:
		    - A giant temple that the people of Daascae believe will rise to
		    the sky. It is shaped like a giant spinning top when in the ground,
		    serving as a complicated prison for an evil powerful entity.
		    When it rises to the sky, it changes its shape and becomes bigger. Parts
		    from outside the city join with it and it expands and transforms into
		    a complicated deadly maze, with traps everywhere, and gaps that lead to
		    a 4 thousand foot fall.
        
        
    Durmia
        - The Durmian Civilization was an ancient race of humans that were extremely
	technologically advanced; even more so than their foreunners, harnessing magika
	as an energy source to power their civilzation. Unlike their ancestors the
	Inusol, they typically were spread out more towards the northern, cold parts of
	the world.
	The Durmia people themselves are descended from only a small branch of Inusol that
	dwelled in the desert, Inusol extent reaches unkown bounds, potentially even
	other worlds.
        
        Dur Remida
            - The most numeruous and powerful branch of Durmia widely agreed upon by
	    scholars, spreading out throughmany different parts of the world.
	    They had many complicated systems of transportation throught the world
	    (mostly underground) linking most of the other Durmia branches.
        
        Dur Aldia:
            - A branch of Durmia that resided at the south edge of the Boreanlands not far
	    from the current Altarian Kingdom. The name "Altarian" orginated from Dur
	    Aldia, as the Dur Aldians are ancestors of Altarian people. The Dur Adlia led
            the Durmian effort to migrate to the the world Valaar.
        
        Dur Kaesa:
            - A branch of Durmia that resided mostly in the Tundra, with structures
            reaching all the way to the northenmost parts of the world, even the Arctic.
	    Their structures and architecture differs greatly from the other
	    Durmian branches, this may be caused by the fact that Dur Kaesa was the
	    most seperated branch from the other ones, having an almost completely
	    isolated system from the rest of Durmian civilization.
        
        Dur Vahlta:
            - A branch of Durmia spread out roughly in a line spanning all the way from the
	    Desert to the Greenlands, they fought a civil war with the Durmia over
	    the control of Aetherium, but were attacked and nearly wiped out by the other
	    branches of Durmia.
	    Most scholars agree they were trapped in their own underground cities and mines,
	    because of the attacks from the other branches, having no other supplies to
	    survive off of but raw Aetherium.
	    It is thought that when they became trapped underground that: the combination of
	    the Aetherium they lived off of, and the underground environment, turned the
	    Dur Vahlta people into hideous abomanations, monsters.

	    Vahl Labyrinthia:
	        - a massive and dangerous labyrinth built into the ground, with automated
		sentries guarding the top of the labyrinth making passage above impossible.
		It is unkown why the labyrinth was built, or what purpose it serves, but
		it is an extremely dangerous place inside and outside.

	    Hall dur Vrendzen:
	       - a mysterious Vahlta ruin located in the mountain range north of
	       Sokorea. The existence of this place was lost to many, except the people
	       of Sokorea, who only know rumours of what may lie in the deep ruins in
	       the cold harsh mountain range.
        
        
        
        
        
        
        
        
